==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Commensuration
<hw>Com*men`su*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>commensuration</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of commensurating; the
state of being commensurate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All fitness lies in a particular <qex>commensuration</qex>, or
proportion of one thing to another.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Comment</ent>⟦br⟧
